'''Kalabsh 2''' (''Handcuff''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.madamasr.com/en/2017/06/03/feature/culture/madas-ramadan-tv-tips-2017-what-to-watch-and-what-to-drop/|title=Mada’s Ramadan TV tips 2017: What to watch and what to drop|work=Mada Masr|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref>) is a 2018 Egyptian TV-Series, a sequel to [[Kalabsh (Egyptian TV-Series)|Kalabsh]], which was aired on the previous Ramadan season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cairoscene.com/ArtsAndCulture/Ramadan-Moslsalat-Guide-2018|title=Ramadan Mosalsalat Guide 2018|website=Cairo Scene|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> It was directed by Peter Mimy and written by Baher Dewidar. It was one of the most recognized shows during Ramadan season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.egypttoday.com/Article/4/50314/%E2%80%98Kalabsh-Part-II%E2%80%99-acheives-highest-viewership-on-YouTube|title=‘Kalabsh Part II’ acheives highest viewership on YouTube - Egypt Today|website=www.egypttoday.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>
A third season was announced to be aired in Ramadan 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mbc.net/ar/programs/kalabsh-2/articles/%D8%A3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%AA%D8%B2%D9%85-%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%AC%D8%B2%D8%A1-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%84--%D9%83%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B4-.html|title=أمير كرارة يعتزم تقديم جزء جديد من مسلسل "كلبش"|website=www.mbc.net|language=ar|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>
==Production==
Director Peter Mimy previously announced the title of the season would be Pasha Masr" (a title was repeatedly given to Slim Al Ansari by deputy officer Zenaty, it means: [[Pasha]] of Egypt, but then they stuck with original Kalabsh. Maya Zaki (Daughter of actress Rojina) worked in the film as in costumes department. The season introduced Haitham Zaki (Son of [[Ahmed Zaki (actor)|Ahmed Zaki]]) as Aref Abu El Ez and Rojina as Leyla El Shimi.
==Overview== The season revolves more around the patriot personality of officer Slim El Ansari ([[Amir Karara]]), and on subjects like Islamic radical groups ([[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIS]], [[Al-Nusra Front|Al-Nusra]], and others) and with an emphasis on their ideology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mbc.net/ar/programs/kalabsh-2/articles/%D9%81%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%81%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D8%B1%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%B4%D9%81%D9%87%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B7%D9%81%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%B3-%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%81.html|title=فلسفة الجماعات الإرهابية يكشفها مصطفى الجاسوس لعاكف|website=www.mbc.net|language=ar|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> The 30 episodes series was officially well-received by [[Egypt]]ian police force.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.egyptindependent.com/police-officers-celebrate-kalabsh-series-amir-karara/|title=Police officers celebrate 'Kalabsh' series with Amir Karara - Egypt Independent|date=2017-06-23|work=Egypt Independent|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref>
